    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Irigoyen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Christiancy</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-06-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 4, 1879</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your excellency’s dispatch No. 6, of the 1st instant, received yesterday, in
                    which your excellency communicates the opinion of your government upon the use
                    of the flag by foreign vessels, according to the laws of the United States of
                    America.</p>
                <p>I have transcribed its contents and the note of the Department of State in
                    Washington, to the minister of war and marine, and I take advantage of this
                    occasion to reiterate to your excellency the assurance of my high regard and
                    esteem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. IRIGOYEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
